'''Brainworm Rot Type A''' was a [[Death/Legends|fatal]] [[Atmosphere/Legends|airborne]] [[Disease/Legends|disease]] that was a subtype of the [[Brainrot Plague]] which afflicted [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoids]] and [[Cephalopod/Legends|cephalopods]] with high levels of [[dialogen]] in their [[Blood/Legends|bloodstream]], including [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidians]], [[Anomid/Legends|Anomids]], and [[Wol Cabasshite/Legends|Wol Cabasshites]]. Symptoms included nausea, cold sweats, the inability to process written instructions, syntax errors in spoken and written communication, and isolated purpling of gills and blowholes.

During the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]], the great number of refugees traveling to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] created an outbreak of the virus in the [[Manarai Heights/Legends|Manarai Heights]] district.

The disease could be evolved from [[Brainworm Rot Type B]] if left unchecked. Like [[Brainworm Rot Type C]], it is likely that this malady originated on [[Neimoidia/Legends|Neimoidia]].

